Key Takeaways

At-Most-Once → unsafe (loss possible)

At-Least-Once → retry safe but duplicates

Exactly-Once → ideal but complex

Banking uses → At-Least-Once + Idempotency

Prevents double transfer

Ensures money safety

What is Idempotency?

Same request executed multiple times → result stays SAME

In banking:

Transfer ₹1000 with txnId = TXN123


If request comes again:

System detects TXN123 already processed → ignore duplicate


So no double debit / credit.

Why duplicates happen in real systems

User double-click transfer

Network timeout → client retries

Server retries

Kafka re-delivery

Load balancer retry

Mobile app resubmits request

Without idempotency → double money transfer 💥

Banking Rule

Every transfer MUST have:

Unique transactionId (Idempotency Key)

Idempotency Flow (Industry Standard)
1. Client sends txnId + transfer request
2. System checks DB:
   → txnId exists? YES → return old result
   → NO → process transfer
3. Save txnId + status

DB Table Design (Important)
transactions
-------------
